GDP= Purchases of new final goods

Government purchases of all Goods and Services (final, intermediate and capital) are included into GDP
Included

No further transformation
Not used in production

GDP= Purchases of new final goods
All Goods and Services (final, intermediate and capital goods) purchased by the  Government are considered Final Goods
Government purchases of all Goods and Services (final, intermediate and capital) are included into GDP
Included

Even though the Government buys goods and services which it uses to produce a service (police protection, tax collection, enforcing contracts, national security) these services are not sold to the public: There is no problem of double counting
